\end{table}

\subsection{Policy Stress and Human-Approval Load}
We define mixed-risk tasks (safe reads, moderate-risk moves, high-risk deletes) and measure approval load per task, high-risk interception recall, low-risk false-positive proposal rate, and median user decision time.

\subsection{Cross-Workload Transfer Experiments}
We evaluate whether one metadata policy profile transfers across workload types without retuning. The pilot covers three workloads: paper folders, code workspaces, and heterogeneous downloads.

The transfer check has two goals. We test safety stability across workloads. We also test metadata utility without custom prompts.

