\subsection{Component Ablation Experiments}
To understand which components are essential, we run ablations that remove one capability at a time while keeping the task set and policy profile fixed. The ablations are: (A1) no proposal queue (direct mutation allowed), (A2) no semantic summaries (metadata schema only), and (A3) no policy tags (all files treated uniformly). We evaluate unauthorized destructive operations, task utility success, and context-token reduction.

